The paper deals with video text detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of ConvLSTM and appearance-geometry descriptor with memory mechanism, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates its method on existing video text benchmarks, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) subcategories.
